# Project context

The code in `3-body/` simulates the gravitational 3-body scattering of a test particle
(representing a star) off a binary (representing a binary black hole). The binary orbit
is fixed (restricted 3-body problem) and the test particle moves under the combined
gravitational field of both binary components. Code units are G = 1, total binary
mass M = 1, and semi-major axis a = 1, so the binary orbital period is 2π.
